.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-compress 1  "rom-weaver-compress "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-compress \- Create a supported archive or disc\-image container
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver compress\fR [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] <\fB\-\-output\fR> [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-codec\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIINPUT\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a supported archive or disc\-image container
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Output container format (derived from the output extension when omitted; required when the output has no recognizable extension; overrides the extension with a warning when they disagree)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Output container path
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-codec\fR \fI<CODEC>\fR
Compression codec override; supports codec[:level]. Repeat \-\-codec for multiple codecs (for example CHD: \-\-codec cdzs[:19] \-\-codec cdzl \-\-codec cdfl). If :level is omitted, falls back to \-\-level profile.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-level\fR \fI<LEVEL>\fR [default: max]
Global compression level profile (min|very\-low|low|medium|high|very\-high|max)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
min
.IP \(bu 2
very\-low
.IP \(bu 2
low
.IP \(bu 2
medium
.IP \(bu 2
high
.IP \(bu 2
very\-high
.IP \(bu 2
max
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIINPUT\fR>
Input file(s) to place in the output container
